Hi,
I am trying to build ddccontrol-0.4.2 on Slackware-12.0, which has the 
"new" pci-utils-2.2.5. First, configure did not detect the pci library and 
aborted. After some googling, I found the following patch at 
www.slax.org/forum, which claims to fix this problem:

--- configure.ac   2006-07-27 20:45:07.000000000 +0000
+++ configure.ac.new   2007-08-03 15:31:00.666636837 +0000
@@ -101,7 +101,7 @@
  DDCPCI=
  if test x$support_ddcpci = xyes; then
     AC_CHECK_HEADERS([pci/pci.h], [], [AC_MSG_ERROR([PCI utils headers not 
found, please install pci-utils.], [1])], [])
-   AC_CHECK_LIB([pci], [pci_alloc], [], [AC_MSG_ERROR([PCI utils library 
not found, please install pci-utils.], [1])])
+   AC_CHECK_LIB([pci], [pci_alloc], [USE_LIBPCI=yes])
     DDCPCI=ddcpci
     AC_DEFINE_UNQUOTED(HAVE_DDCPCI, 1, [Define if ddccontrol is built with 
ddcpci support.])
  fi

After applying the patch and running autoconf, configure now detected the 
pci library (/usr/lib/libpci.a), however, make ended up with the 
following link error:


gcc -g -O2 -Wall -DDATADIR=\"/usr/local/share/ddccontrol-db\" 
-DBINDIR=\"/usr/local/bin\" -o ddcpci -Wl,-z -Wl,now main.o nvidia.o 
radeon.o i2c-algo-bit.o intel810.o via.o sis.o
  main.o: In function `main':
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:275: undefined reference 
to `pci_alloc'
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:276: undefined reference 
to `pci_init'
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:277: undefined reference 
to `pci_scan_bus'
main.o: In function `list':
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:221: undefined reference 
to `pci_fill_info'
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:222: undefined reference 
to `pci_read_word'
main.o: In function `open_card':
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:124: undefined reference 
to `pci_fill_info'
/usr/local/src/ddccontrol-0.4.2/src/ddcpci/main.c:125: undefined reference 
to `pci_read_word'
