There is no shared library in Debian.

http://packages.debian.org/sid/pciutils/i386/filelist
http://packages.debian.org/sid/pciutils-dev/i386/filelist

Neither list shows a shared library.  I seem to recall that this caused
a problem in one of my packages previously where there would be
unresolved symbol errors since libpci depends on libz, but the package
itself did not.  So, everything would compile, but then the linking step
would fail.  Supposedly this sort of thing is a problem for static
libraries.

Regards,

